rComments: Prof. Jeffries is extremely nice and approachable, our lectures were 3 hours long but she kept them interesting and gave us breaks throughout. Learned alot in her class and would definitely take any class with her again.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Gives good feedback', 'Participation matters']

rComments: Fiona was amazing, the lectures were great and she was so kind to our class (gave us all a 2+ week extension on the paper). The midterm is open book, and there are 5 quizzes worth 5% each but she drops your lowest mark. Super easy to do well if you just do the readings before hand. You'll love this class, but I recommend going to her office hours!

Amazing prof, she encouraged class discussions, used a lot of videos and media to make the class more interesting. Her TA was a tough grader, and unless you see her in her office hours, which she strongly encourages, the grading criteria isn't super clear.

I found her classes quite interesting and she is good a engaging the classroom. It was her first time teaching the course so it was a little bit too much of a discussion class for me. I found her grading to be quite tough and she definitely made me work for it. Pop quizes on readings (20%), research paper (40%), outline (10%) and midterm (30%).

rComments: An amazing professor. Cared about her students, very accessible. Lectures were very interesting and relevant, used a mix of videos, discussion, guest lecturers and her own lectures to teach. All readings were online and free as well as being interesting. Did not post slides so attendance was important but not mandatory. Would highly recommend.
